                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1826</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Russell</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-17T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department concurs in view expressed in your May 15, 4 p.m., regarding
                    presidential election and endorsed by Admiral Caperton, Your action may be
                    guided accordingly.</p>
                <p>Your May 1, 2 p.m., May 2, 6 p.m., Department’s May 7, noon, and your May 10, 11
                    a.m. Report your opinion whether, if exercise of executive power by ministers
                    proves inadvisable or fails to ensure method of government desired, the
                    exigencies of present situation warrant consideration of validity of resignation
                    of President in light of provisions of Article 50, Dominican Constitution and of
                    your interpretation of true sentiments of Congress.</p>
                <p>Your May 7, 4 a.m. Preparatory to permanent reforms, upon which we must insist,
                    and in view of recent developments, also report whether complete disarmament of
                    the revolutionary element throughout the country may now be opportunely
                    effected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
